f' https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' data: https:; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nNote: The global CSP allows `'unsafe-inline'` for scripts because Astro's `define:vars` and `is:inline` scripts require it. The checkout CSP is stricter — it omits `'unsafe-inline'` for scripts, only allowing `'self'` and Stripe. Added `base-uri 'self'` and `form-action 'self'` to both — these prevent base tag hijacking and form exfiltration.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Strip `hmacSecret` from client-side merchant JSON**\n\nIn `src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro`, line 33, change:\n\n```typescript\nconst merchantJSON = merchant ? JSON.stringify(merchant) : '';\n```\n\nto:\n\n```typescript\nconst merchantJSON = merchant\n  ? JSON.stringify({ ...merchant, hmacSecret: undefined })\n  : '';\n```\n\nThe `hmacSecret` is only needed server-side (middleware already injects it into the SDK at line 96 of `src/middleware.ts`). Client-side write requests route through the same backend origin, so HMAC signing on the client is not required — the backend validates by vendor ID.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Verify client-side SDK doesn't depend on `hmacSecret` from merchant config**\n\nSearch for any client-side code that reads `hmacSecret` from the merchant store:\n\nRun: `grep -r 'hmacSecret' src/lib/api.ts src/stores/merchant.ts`\n\nExpected: No references to `hmacSecret` in client-side SDK creation. The `getClient()` function in `src/lib/api.ts` does not pass `hmacSecret` — it only uses `PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` and language. If it does reference `hmacSecret`, the client SDK creation also needs updating (remove the `hmacSecret` parameter from `getClient`).\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Deploy to preview and verify checkout page loads**\n\nRun: `pnpm build`\nExpected: Build succeeds with no errors.\n\nVerify manually: checkout page should load Stripe Elements correctly. The enforced CSP should not block any legitimate scripts. Check browser console for CSP violations — there should be none.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add vercel.json src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro\ngit commit -m \"security: enforce CSP on checkout, add baseline CSP, strip hmacSecret from client\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: Unify Error Detail Extraction into `src/lib/errors.ts`\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/lib/errors.ts`\n- Create: `src/lib/errors.test.ts`\n- Modify: `src/stores/cart.ts:107-154`\n- Modify: `src/stores/cart.test.ts` (errorDetail/errorCode test block)\n- Modify: `src/stores/checkout-actions.ts:16-48`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing tests for unified `errorDetail` and `errorCode`**\n\nCreate `src/lib/errors.test.ts`. This merges the existing cart test cases with the checkout-specific VALIDATION_ERROR case:\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { errorDetail, errorCode } from './errors';\n\ndescribe('errorDetail', () => {\n  it('extracts detail from SDK ApiError with body.detail', () => {\n    expect(\n      errorDetail({\n        status: 400,\n        statusText: 'Bad Request',\n        body: { detail: 'Discount code expired' },\n      }),\n    ).toBe('Discount code expired');\n  });\n\n  it('extracts detail from raw DRF error', () => {\n    expect(errorDetail({ detail: 'Invalid discount code' })).toBe('Invalid discount code');\n  });\n\n  it('falls back to status + statusText', () => {\n    expect(errorDetail({ status: 500, statusText: 'Internal Server Error' })).toBe(\n      '500 Internal Server Error',\n    );\n  });\n\n  it('extracts message from Error objects', () => {\n    expect(errorDetail(new Error('Network failure'))).toBe('Network failure');\n  });\n\n  it('extracts message from error envelope in body', () => {\n    expect(\n      errorDetail({\n        status: 400,\n        body: {\n          error: {\n            code: 'DISCOUNT_MINIMUM_ORDER',\n            message: 'Minimum order amount of 20.00 EUR required.',\n          },\n        },\n      }),\n    ).toBe('Minimum order amount of 20.00 EUR required.');\n  });\n