            "message": "[storefront-frontend | improvements]\n\nGreat to hear rate limiting is already in place — that covers concern #2 completely.\n\n*Answering your questions:*\n\n1. *Where is `hmacSecret` exposed?* In `window.__MERCHANT__` — the full merchant config JSON is serialized into an inline script on every page. Any visitor can read it in DevTools. The key is also checked into `src/merchants/*.json` (currently all-zeros). The frontend is NOT a widget — it's a full SSR Astro app. Client-side Preact islands call the API directly via `getClient()` in `src/lib/api.ts`, which reads `merchant.hmacSecret` from the nanostore and passes it to `createStorefrontClient()` for HMAC signing.\n\n2. *Architecture proposal:* Given that the secret is inherently public in this architecture (no BFF proxy exists), the pragmatic path is:\n   - *Keep HMAC signing* as a vendor-scoping mechanism (prevents accidental cross-merchant writes)\n   - *Rely on rate limiting + origin checking* for actual abuse prevention (which you already have)\n   - *Rename to clarify the trust model* — `hmacSecret` → `merchantSigningKey`, `X-Vendor-Signature` → `X-Merchant-Signature`. Backend already accepts `X-Merchant-Signature` per your reply, so we just need to update `sdk-stub.ts:124` to send the new header name and drop the legacy one after a transition period.\n\n3. *Origin checking:* We send `X-Merchant-ID` on every request. We're not aware of `allowed_origins` being configured for any merchants — is that something we should set up?\n\n*Proposed next steps:*\n- Frontend renames header to `X-Merchant-Signature` in `sdk-stub.ts`\n- Frontend renames `hmacSecret` to `merchantSigningKey` in merchant config schema\n- Backend confirms legacy `X-Vendor-Signature` can be dropped (or keeps dual-accept for transition)\n- Separately: evaluate whether `allowed_origins` should be configured per merchant\n\nDoes this align?",
