locals;\n\n// Fetch comms and collections in parallel — eliminates sequential waterfall\nimport { fetchCommsMessages } from '@/lib/comms-fetch';\n\nconst [commsMessages, { sections: menuSections, source }] = await Promise.all([\n  fetchCommsMessages(sdk),\n  fetchCollectionsOrCategories(sdk),\n]);\n\nconst sectionProducts = await Promise.all(\n  menuSections.map(async (section) => {\n    const result =\n      source === 'collections'\n        ? await sdk.GET(`/api/v1/collections/{slug}/products/`, {\n            params: { path: { slug: section.slug } },\n          })\n        : await sdk.GET('/api/v1/products/', {\n            params: { query: section.id ? { category: String(section.id) } : {} },\n          });\n\n    if (result.error) {\n      console.error(`[index] failed to fetch products for \"${section.name}\"`, result.error);\n    }\n    const raw = (result.data as { results: Array<Record<string, unknown>> } | null)?.results ?? [];\n    return { category: section, products: raw.map(normalizeProduct) };\n  }),\n);\n```\n\nThen pass `commsMessages` to `BaseLayout` (line 52):\n\n```astro\n<BaseLayout title={merchant.name} description={merchant.seo.defaultDescription} commsMessages={commsMessages}>\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Build and verify**\n\nRun: `pnpm build`\nExpected: Build succeeds. The menu page now fetches comms and collections in parallel.\n\nRun: `pnpm test`\nExpected: All tests pass.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro src/pages/[lang]/index.astro\ngit commit -m \"perf: parallelize comms + collections fetch on menu page\n\nEliminates sequential SSR waterfall: comms and collections now\nfetch via Promise.all instead of sequentially across layout and\npage frontmatter. Non-menu pages fall back to inline fetch.\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: Switch Google Fonts to Non-Render-Blocking Loading\n\nThe current `<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href={googleFontsUrl} />` blocks rendering until the CSS file downloads from `fonts.googleapis.com`. On 3G, this adds ~300-600ms to FCP. The `&display=swap` parameter in the URL already tells the browser to use fallback fonts while loading, but the stylesheet itself is still render-blocking.\n\nThe fix: use the media-attribute swap technique — load with `media=\"print\"` (non-blocking), then swap to `media=\"all\"` on load.\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro:106-108`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Replace render-blocking font stylesheet with async loading**\n\nIn `src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro`, replace lines 106-108:\n\n```astro\n{googleFontsUrl && <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\" />}\n{googleFontsUrl && <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.gstatic.com\" crossorigin />}\n{googleFontsUrl && <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href={googleFontsUrl} />}\n```\n\nwith:\n\n```astro\n{googleFontsUrl && <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\" />}\n{googleFontsUrl && <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.gstatic.com\" crossorigin />}\n{googleFontsUrl && (\n  <>\n    <link\n      rel=\"stylesheet\"\n      href={googleFontsUrl}\n      media=\"print\"\n      onload=\"this.media='all'\"\n    />\n    <noscript><link rel=\"stylesheet\" href={googleFontsUrl} /></noscript>\n  </>\n)}\n```\n\nThis technique:\n- `media=\"print\"` makes the browser download the stylesheet without blocking render\n- `onload=\"this.media='all'\"` swaps it to active once downloaded\n- `<noscript>` fallback ensures fonts load when JS is disabled\n- The `&display=swap` in the URL ensures text is visible immediately with system fonts\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Build and verify**\n\nRun: `pnpm build`\nExpected: Build succeeds.\n\nTest manually: page should render immediately with system/fallback fonts, then swap to custom fonts once downloaded. There should be a brief FOUT (Flash of Unstyled Text) which is the correct tradeoff for 3G users.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro\ngit commit -m \"perf: